We further recommended that the Municipal Accountant and the Supply Officer/Municipal Treasurer undertake immediate reconciliation of the PPE per physical inventory conducted as against the property ledger cards and property cards and effect adjustments, if any, to reflect the correct balances of PPE accounts as reflected in the financial statements.

We recommended that the inventory committee:
1. Summarize the result of the physical inventory count per PPE account to come up with the complete list of PPEs;
2. Reconcile the physical count with the records maintained by the Supply Officer/Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant;  
3. Submit the RPCPPE containing the complete list of PPEs with technical descriptions and specifications in conformity with the provisions of Chapter 7 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGU, Volume I.
We further recommended that the Municipal Accountant and the Supply Officer/Municipal Treasurer undertake immediate reconciliation of the PPE per physical inventory conducted as against the property ledger cards and property cards and effect adjustments, if any, to reflect the correct balances of PPE accounts as reflected in the financial statements.
